#memory box

~ block_talk_no_aida
Player: Umm.. I think I should talk to the Nurse before I talk to anyone else.
=> END

~ block_talk_no_memory_box
Player: I don't think I need to talk to them right now.
Player: The Nurse told me to 'use' the memory box. Better do that first.
=> END

~ block_memory_box_no_aida
Player: I should probably talk to the nurse before I touch this weird machine.
=> END

~ memory_box_unlocked
You slide the TechPass into the card slot.

Memory Box: Please place the headset on.

You pick up the strange device and place it over your head.

Player: (Alright... here goes.)
Player: (If this thing works...)
Player: (I might finally remember who I am.)

=> END
~ memory_box_locked
Player: (Hmmm. The screen says I need to insert my TechPass™ to begin.)

if GameManager.get_current_level_flag("learned_techpass_from_aida") == true and GameManager.get_current_level_flag("learned_techpass_from_sergey") == true
	Player: (This must be the card the Nurse and Sergey were talking about.)
elif GameManager.get_current_level_flag("learned_techpass_from_aida") == true
	Player: (This must be the card the Nurse mentioned.)
elif GameManager.get_current_level_flag("learned_techpass_from_sergey") == true
	Player: (This must be the card Sergey was talking about.)
else
	Player: (Fuck is that, now?)

do GameManager.set_current_level_flag("has_tried_memory_box", true)
=> END

